1
00:00:44,620 --> 00:00:46,750
I'm amazed we got permission to exhume the body.

2
00:00:46,750 --> 00:00:50,840
It's backwards. They disregarded
our investigation by burying him to begin with.

3
00:00:50,840 --> 00:00:54,740
Yes, sir. Still, a military cemetery...

4
00:00:55,430 --> 00:00:59,850
It's ridiculously expensive to dispose of
a prosthetic body that can't be reused.

5
00:00:59,850 --> 00:01:03,270
Thanks to their cost-cutting,
we can recover the cyberbrain.

6
00:01:03,270 --> 00:01:04,160
Where are the engineers?

7
00:01:06,230 --> 00:01:08,230
Drawing straws at HQ.

8
00:01:08,230 --> 00:01:12,110
Apparently connecting to a dead criminal's
cyberbrain is "creepy".

9
00:01:12,110 --> 00:01:14,090
We don't know yet that he's a criminal.

10
00:01:14,630 --> 00:01:16,180
Chief Aramaki!

11
00:01:16,180 --> 00:01:18,550
We'll check the contents,
then take it back to headquarters.

12
00:01:25,040 --> 00:01:27,370
What are you waiting for?
Put it down!

13
00:01:28,920 --> 00:01:30,420
Sorry, sir!

14
00:01:31,800 --> 00:01:34,240
Don't open that coffin!

15
00:03:23,660 --> 00:03:25,350
This is from your unit.

16
00:04:11,100 --> 00:04:12,770
Are you military?

17
00:04:16,630 --> 00:04:19,420
I'm Aramaki, with Public Security Section 9.

18
00:04:19,420 --> 00:04:23,240
We're investigating
Lieutenant Colonel Mamuro's murder.

19
00:04:23,240 --> 00:04:25,450
I'm seizing his cyberbrain
and prosthetic body as evidence.

20
00:04:25,740 --> 00:04:30,470
He's also suspected of taking bribes,
and we're investigating that too.

21
00:04:30,470 --> 00:04:32,980
Public Security has no right to ransack this
place.


22
00:04:32,980 --> 00:04:35,400
We'll bury him again when the case is closed.

23
00:04:35,400 --> 00:04:38,820
And how do I know you won't pull a cover-up,
or fabricate evidence?

24
00:04:38,820 --> 00:04:42,670
The military is in the middle of
its first major shakeup since the war.

25
00:04:42,970 --> 00:04:47,870
It would be more suspicious
if this only got an internal investigation.

26
00:04:47,870 --> 00:04:50,890
If he were still with us,
Mamuro would have been the first to say so.

27
00:04:51,450 --> 00:04:53,120
You knew him?

28
00:04:53,120 --> 00:04:55,640
Yes, back when I was an Army man.

29
00:04:55,640 --> 00:04:59,110
There's not a soldier in the world
more squeaky-clean than he was.

30
00:05:04,260 --> 00:05:06,470
Your name and unit?

31
00:05:08,280 --> 00:05:12,180
Major Motoko Kusanagi, Unit 501.

32
00:05:13,730 --> 00:05:17,330
501? So you were his subordinate.

33
00:05:19,860 --> 00:05:21,780
Open it up.

34
00:05:21,780 --> 00:05:24,150
Can I ask your rank?

35
00:05:24,150 --> 00:05:26,780
I was in the old Investigations Section.
That's all.

36
00:05:26,780 --> 00:05:30,510
They sold off whatever wouldn't fit
in the coffin to a junk shop.

37
00:05:42,900 --> 00:05:44,070
That's not his body!

38
00:06:08,740 --> 00:06:10,050
Get down!

39
00:07:02,230 --> 00:07:05,420
Finally back on base, you delinquent?

40
00:07:05,420 --> 00:07:08,340
Why did you authorize Public Security's
involvement?!


41
00:07:08,340 --> 00:07:12,590
Since I can't dismiss the possibility
that Mamuro was corrupt, I had no choice.

42
00:07:12,590 --> 00:07:15,600
Unit 501 should be investigating this!

43
00:07:16,540 --> 00:07:19,290
The higher-ups told us to stay out of it.

44
00:07:20,770 --> 00:07:23,400
Someone set a trap at his grave.

45
00:07:23,400 --> 00:07:24,400
Ignore it.

46
00:07:24,400 --> 00:07:26,420
His cyberbrain is gone!

47
00:07:27,030 --> 00:07:29,070
This isn't the time to
stir up a hornet's nest.

48
00:07:30,240 --> 00:07:33,370
Then you believe that
he was taking dirty money?

49
00:07:33,370 --> 00:07:36,890
He got mugged downtown.
That much is fact.

50
00:07:37,240 --> 00:07:42,520
Not an honorable death, but compared
to indictment, maybe he got lucky.

51
00:07:42,520 --> 00:07:46,340
Thanks to him,
our letters of recommendation are on hold, too.

52
00:07:46,340 --> 00:07:48,920
Concentrate on your work for now.

53
00:07:48,920 --> 00:07:49,820
Work?

54
00:07:50,780 --> 00:07:55,280
I distinctly remember asking you to
analyze that infected hardware.

55
00:07:55,660 --> 00:07:59,750
Not possible.
I just got back to Japan today, you know.

56
00:08:01,520 --> 00:08:03,310
True enough.

57
00:08:03,310 --> 00:08:04,860
I'll do the assignment.

58
00:08:04,860 --> 00:08:08,650
In return, give me leave to go off-base
and authorize direct debit.

59
00:08:08,650 --> 00:08:10,170
Such a problem child.

60
00:08:10,510 --> 00:08:13,930
I'm only going to find out who set the trap.

61
00:08:13,930 --> 00:08:17,640
Very well.
I'll take care of it in Mamuro's place.

62
00:08:17,640 --> 00:08:19,540
Thanks, Kurutsu.

63
00:08:20,970 --> 00:08:24,000
Don't forget your meeting with the brass.

64
00:09:50,540 --> 00:09:53,210
Giichi Mamuro, member of
a special unit of the GSDA,

65
00:09:53,210 --> 00:09:56,130
was murdered on the fifth of this month.

66
00:09:56,130 --> 00:09:59,680
Lieutenant Colonel Mamuro is suspected of taking
large bribes...


67
00:09:56,130 --> 00:09:59,680
Niihama police say the investigation into
his possible corruption is ongoing.

68
00:09:59,680 --> 00:10:03,290
...while serving as a security official
in Harimadara's weapons export--

69
00:10:39,380 --> 00:10:42,050
Access records of his movements
on the day of his death

70
00:10:42,050 --> 00:10:44,160
and all data from city surveillance cameras.

71
00:11:12,790 --> 00:11:13,980
He was tailed.

72
00:11:14,400 --> 00:11:18,490
Scan anyone who traveled
the same route he did before time of death.

73
00:11:23,680 --> 00:11:24,860
Three...

74
00:11:35,320 --> 00:11:36,250
A fourth?

75
00:12:09,430 --> 00:12:13,000
Three men and a mobile land mine
were following him?

